<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A0CF4E06-375D-4F8F-9407-FAC17310F5FF" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A0CF4E06-375D-4F8F-9407-FAC17310F5FF" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install the Colorado printer driver in ONYX</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M028334-B18"><p class="- topic/p ">Install the Colorado driver on the ONYX RIP. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This Colorado system requires ONYX 22. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-2E6BFA7C-FC72-4B97-A8CB-F0EC7C45FC91"><p class="- topic/p ">The screen dumps in this procedure are of the Colorado 1640. The procedure is similar for this Colorado system. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-C71E4B56-F6A6-429E-9630-3F0443D53874" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_5CF05B1DAFBC41A4B310C4B8A0E6A51B" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_C1EE3D99F2904CF6967E60F12334240E" class="- topic/li "/><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> It is advised to do this task together with the customer ONYX specialist available. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The list of media the customer will use. A filled out Site Preparation Guide will provide this information. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> ONYX must be available. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Either 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> A PC with ONYX installed must be available at the customer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> ONYX has to be operational at the customer and the driver is added to an existing ONYX configuration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">or 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> a PC with ONYX installed must be delivered to the customer. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The ONYX version has to be checked for compliance with the system software release. 
</p></li><li id="LI_720890BF721F4E4998FA9AC235FA9E44" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Colorado 1635/1655 PrnInst file must be available. 
</p><note id="GUID-11DAE181-B120-4E27-A8E9-AACC63BA05DF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> The prninst file contains a driver and media profiles. You can always download the latest PrnInst file and select the media you need using the ONYX Printer &amp; Profile Download Manager. 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-5089E63C-F553-4F8E-9480-0C0EDBDC9D89" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C603724A-FCC8-4F2D-9A7E-4EF3281D9469-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C603724A-FCC8-4F2D-9A7E-4EF3281D9469-low.png"/></fig><note id="GUID-703BB38F-0631-4E73-A443-A3322C18BD22" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> The list of media displayed, depends on the selected Profile Provider. 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_CAC4B2ED6A984A9D90ECACDDA4CDA01F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Administrator rights within ONYX are required for the driver installation and configuration. 
</p><note id="GUID-8F030F55-688B-4436-9629-B66D125D8785" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> ONYX has to be used with administrator rights (not only for installing a driver). This has to be configured after the installation. If you have to provide administrator credentials when launching ONYX, then they have to be available or the customer has to enter them. 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_CF01B3EB5B9C4CC88128EA09CBE14C40" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The TCP/IP settings (name or address) of the system 
</p></li><li id="LI_8731D93931D847A1AFD1EFBFB41F7685" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The system is installed, connected to the network and ready to print 
</p></li><li id="LI_4B03996D878549C7BD5DB682FF4CE807" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Media (e.g. IJM613 roll of 1600 mm) is not loaded. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-3EEB21D9-E71E-44E2-AAB5-43C134D0B0AB" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not change any settings within ONYX that can influence the current workflow of the customer. Stick to the procedure as stated. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-94C20406-75A1-4BD0-A7DB-8CD9777F04B0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Installation procedure </title><table id="NEW" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure that ONYX is not active. If active: de-activate it. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Select the Colorado M-series PrnInst file.
</p><fig id="FIG_A8E77317EC224D038F95DC484B80B5C7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6DFA67B7-7D82-4F6F-864F-920DF2B450EA-low.png" id="IMAGE_CEBAB20C62524FA8890D67E933922341" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6DFA67B7-7D82-4F6F-864F-920DF2B450EA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Select all the tick boxes for the media the customer will use. 
</p><fig id="GUID-03051E30-930E-41BD-B4A1-9766D72807A9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-16C1116C-E7E8-498F-9CE1-634A1A4AD363-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-16C1116C-E7E8-498F-9CE1-634A1A4AD363-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verify your standard media type is part of the listed media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If yes: select Install 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If no: contact your service product specialist. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select Install. 
</p><fig id="FIG_5B57B8E13D3C464E8517C3C6B16F521B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C69F177A-C006-487D-A48D-0F02A93E2ACD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C69F177A-C006-487D-A48D-0F02A93E2ACD-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Select Finish. 
</p><fig id="GUID-61432E9F-DACB-4E72-B424-898D0EEF952F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-377933AF-5AD6-4E2A-9BAA-A3E5403C3F2D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-377933AF-5AD6-4E2A-9BAA-A3E5403C3F2D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Thrive RIP-Queue and the Configure Printer Port open. 
</p><fig id="GUID-D8F37B43-8678-4E8C-B8EA-3CC61C2E22A0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0ED7BE02-8276-46C2-9144-7B8AEC8C14AA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0ED7BE02-8276-46C2-9144-7B8AEC8C14AA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Select TCP/IP Printer, next select Configure. 
</p><fig id="GUID-155B63D0-A901-443B-9204-81134812E5A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-22C29A90-4E76-4FDD-B143-387DB0771C24-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-22C29A90-4E76-4FDD-B143-387DB0771C24-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Enter the Host name or IP address (in this example IP-address). 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Leave the &lt;port 9100&gt; setting unchanged. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Select Test. 
</p><note id="GUID-CB992175-FEB0-4CD8-AE73-A03BFF24BE67" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the printer is connected, up and running and has a license. The test will fail otherwise. 
</p></note><fig id="FIG_1CF7EBC802614AE4972DDCD699AC035F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-25AF9464-6D0F-4D4C-832B-309B8D54CBA3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-25AF9464-6D0F-4D4C-832B-309B8D54CBA3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verify the Colorado system is found: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If yes: Valid IP Address Found! Continue with next step. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If no: solve this issue (e.g. use ping command, verify engine network settings, check DNS). 
</p><fig id="FIG_4A6FD4B31DE14639810698622C2BFED1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-58159881-2F14-45D9-BA83-18E59CD88B71-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-58159881-2F14-45D9-BA83-18E59CD88B71-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Select OK. 
</p><fig id="FIG_611F30B03DBA4ACC8C2F83675058381D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8E08AE9C-1C9B-4538-81B2-F1598CB6D8CC-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8E08AE9C-1C9B-4538-81B2-F1598CB6D8CC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verify in Thrive RIP-Queue that the Colorado system status is idle. 
</p><fig id="FIG_C79AEEC3F5154CF1A94938271471DCB0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C25E6A60-D978-41CD-9B9A-7E01F727B647-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C25E6A60-D978-41CD-9B9A-7E01F727B647-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Based on the installed licences of the engine (check on UI), the appropriate options must be selected in the RIP. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In order to open the dialog: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Select involved printer, right-click and select 'Configure Printer …' 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Select tab 'Device', click 'Features' 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Select 'Global Printer Features' and click 'Configure…', the screen below appears 
</p><fig id="GUID-70F7D910-994B-4CF0-B3C0-7DBF867DCB84" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-592C658C-EF49-473A-A414-A507E836C57A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-592C658C-EF49-473A-A414-A507E836C57A-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">FLXfinish+ licence installed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check option ‘Printing with FLXfinish+ and matte print modes' 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> White ink licence installed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Check option ‘Printing with white ink’ 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click ‘OK’ to save to the settings. 
</p></li></ul></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-3140D264-493B-4163-8934-73ACCD3B6AA1.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>